Description: Limestone model of a naos shrine. The surface of the shrine is smooth, with no clear evidence of any incised detail. The deep space carved into the front of the shrine does not appear to have held a figure or object, as there’s no clear socket or base missing from inside the shrine. On the reverse there appears to be faint traces of a painted figure in black, this could possibly represent a scarab figure.
Curator's comments: Further painted decoration may once have been applied to the object that is now faded. Without further stylistic details it is difficult to narrow down a date for the object, though the Late Period has been tentatively suggested.
Acquisition name: Purchased from: Rev Greville John Chester
